5. JolokiaHttpHandler.java:318-325 - sendForbidden writes SecurityException messages to a response with no explicit Content-Type; not a realistic XSS vector.

The JSONP XSS vulnerabilities are critical: any user can craft a URL with ?callback=<malicious_js> and trick a victim into executing arbitrary JavaScript. No authentication is required by default for the Jolokia agent.
